Reasoning: The paper analyzes the altmetric performance of Brazilian publications authored by researchers who are productivity scholarship holders of the National Council of Scientific and Technological Development (CNPq). The study focuses on the online attention data of academic journal articles published between 2016 and October 2017. The paper involves the use of data collection and analysis techniques, which are commonly used in the fields of digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), social media (cs.SI), cybernetics (cs.CY), and scientific data (cs.SD).
